                    <span>my wife is wtc tower two survivor and reading these stories of survival made me realize what she went through that day. She worked on the 85th floor of tower two, and she told me that when the first plane hit tower one she attempted to call 911 but the phones were not working. She got some other people who she worked with and searched the floor for others before they evacuated.They were on there way down the stairs when the p.a. system came on and they were told to return to there office that there was a small fire in tower  one but it's been contained. she did not listen to the p.a announcement and told the others to continue down.Luckily they listened, moments later they reached the 72nd floor and the 2nd plane hit tower two. My wife said the tower swayed back anf forth they heard a loud boom. they then hauled ass and got out 8 minutes before tower two collapsed. i still have a hard time with that day,even though she went through it,she got over it quicker then i did. People she worked with said she was a hero for telling them not to listen to p.a. system and for evacuating the floor and searching for others before leaving. she never saw herself as a hero but i do.If thay had not left the 85th floor when they did they would have been trapped due to the plane hit between 76 and 84th floors. Sadly seven people died from her floor, my wife searched that floor before she left. she said people may have gone down other stairs before she and others left and came up when the p.a system told them to return to the offices. This book is one of the best i've read becuase it comes from the people who lived through it. god bless you all and our hearts go out those who perished and to there loved ones.
<br /></span>
                  
              
